    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Circular depressions pecked into a rock's surface by humans in prehistoric times, sometimes surrounded by concentric circles. These functioned as petroglyphs and were also applied to megaliths.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
